node.text:
I recently started following this bomb.com self help coach on my personal Instagram account. @therealjoirizarry 

Her daily convos/advice/ viewpoints are spot on in this stage of growth and healing. 

This particular post resonates with me as I started setting hella boundaries. Now I can identify that empty feeling, the loss that she speaks of. Maybe you can relate?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas with @tanner_hamilton22, @atxlien, @annmarie_is_social, @therealjoirizarry, and @wherethemobat. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'lea @wherethemobat we're just suicidal mfs telling other suicidal mfs that suicide is not the answer 1:25 pm 08/06/2020 Twitter for iPhone'.

node.text:
TW: Suicide

I know it’s dark. But it’s true. 

If you don’t know I lost my son to death by suicide 11 years ago. The @asafeplaceinsideyourhead family of @tanner_hamilton22 @atxlien and @annmarie_is_social have spent the last two years reminding you that you are not alone, and that you are seen and heard. And also that suicide is not the answer. 

The @asafeplaceinsideyourhead community reaches worldwide and the way you guys engage to help others, cheer each other on, and provide helpful advice is mind blowing. Never in our wildest dreams did we expect this is what it would be like. 

Keep on fighting the good fight, warriors, it’s hard for the sufferers of mental health issues and mental illness. Let’s keep the conversation going and end the stigma. 

Stop 🛑 suicide. 

In this post we honor Kenny brother to @tanner_hamilton22 @atxlien, nephew to @annmarie_is_social and my son. - @therealjoirizarry 

Feel free to honor someone you have loved and lost below 👇🏼

@wherethemobat
.
.
.
.
.
#stopsuicide #suicideprevention #suicideawarness #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #endtheatigmaofmentalhealth #itsoktonotbeok #mentalillness #warriors #asafeplaceinsideyourhead

You 'chilling' means you're probably just ignoring the million things on your to-do list.'.

node.text:
It’s 10:45 PM and I’ve been constantly busy today….it wasn’t a bad day, just no real time to rest. Guess it’s time to lay in bed and think about how I could have done something better. Night time anxiety is great….jk. Goodnight everyone! - @tanner_hamilton22

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas with @cleopatraelixir, and @anxietytwitter. May be an image of text that says 'cathy delkhah @cleopatraelixir you a Stop saying "start a family" when mean have kids. A couple is still family. A single person and her cat is still a family. A couple and their plants are still a family. You dont need kids just to be called a family.'.

node.text:
👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼

The family unit looks so different these days. And personally, for me family looks different too. I have one granddaughter and am perfectly fine with that, I actually discourage my children to have children, fight me! 

UNPOPULAR OPINION… you do you with the family/framily that looks good and is manageable to you. Don’t fall into the social “norms” of what you should do and do what you want to do.

Your mental health will thank you. - @therealjoirizarry 

@anxietytwitter 

📸 @cleopatraelixir 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
I recently started following this bomb.com self help coach on my personal Instagram account. @therealjoirizarry 

Her daily convos/advice/ viewpoints are spot on in this stage of growth and healing. 

This particular post resonates with me as I started setting hella boundaries. Now I can identify that empty feeling, the loss that she speaks of. Maybe you can relate?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'GODFATHER GOTTI! @Gotti2Hottiee same Y'all get irritated with people fast because y'all parents did the with you. Y'all can't communicate because y'all parents couldn't. Y'all think yelling /being aggressive every time u disagree with something is okay because y'all parents yelled/ got hostile when they...'.

node.text:
Not just your parents, but any damaged relationship you still carry with you today. 

As we carry on the generational curse of dysfunction we also teach people how it’s ok to speak to and treat us. We’re giving them our language. 

We don’t have to carry this behavior on. We can say no and treat others how we want to be treated instead of how we are treated. 

Let’s break the cycle. - @therealjoirizarry 

@gottie2hottiee on Twitter 
.
.
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on July 27, 2021 tagging @blkgirllostkeyss9. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'René Brooks Black Girl, Lost Keys @blkgirllostkeys asked my therapist why I couldn't get past something| really needed to get past And we concluded I couldn't admit even to myself how much it hurt. Because didn't want to be hurt. So I refused to be hurt. But here I am years later, hurting. Feel your fucking feelings'.

node.text:
It’s not just the “hurt”that causes you pain.

I  need to feel the betrayal, the heartache, the sadness, the loneliness, the neglect. I need to process all these things.  Give those feelings big girl words. 

Feel it, that thing that you don’t want to, feel it and be free. 

This message is for you and this message is for me. - @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @blackgirllostkeys
